**QA Engineer

UTORG** is a fintech company holding VASP licenses and operating in 187 countries. 

Now we are looking for a **QA Engineer** who will strengthen our team and contribute to the success of our products and the bright future of Web3.

**Work format:** remote
**Employment:** full-time
**Salary range:** 1500-3000 USD

**Work Experience**

**‚óè **Web and mobile application testing, including cross-platform testing (iOS, Android) and cross-browser testing;
**‚óè** Working with emulators and simulators (Android Studio, Xcode, RocketSim);
**‚óè** Work in fintech projects, including work with cryptocurrency wallets, exchanges, payment acceptance systems, and AML systems (SEON, ScoreChain, SumSub);
**‚óè** Agile/Scrum (Scrum Events, Product Backlog, Sprint Backlog, Burndown and Burnup diagrams);
**‚óè** Test documentation systems (TestRail, TestLink, TestIT, Zephyr);
**‚óè** Bug tracking and ticket management systems (Jira, Confluence);
**‚óè** Logging and monitoring systems (Google Console, Grafana, Sentry, BigQuery);
**‚óè** Version control and CI/CD systems (Git, Bitbucket, Jenkins, GitHub, AzureDevOps, CircleCI), including setting up automatic build and test runs;
**‚óè** Tools and frameworks for writing autotests (Selenium, Appium, Cypress, JUnit, TestNG, RestAssured) and creating reports (Allure);
**‚óè** Implementation of alerting and tracking systems.

**Technical Skills**

**‚óè **Versatile testing skills, knowledge of techniques and principles of testing and test design;
**‚óè **Performance, compatibility, UI/GUI and UX testing;
**‚óè **Functional and non-functional API testing;
**‚óè **Regression and Smoke testing;
**‚óè **Working with test artifacts and writing test documentation (TestCase, CheckList, TestPlan);
**‚óè **Knowledge of core automation approaches and practices (POM, DDT);
**‚óè **Working with prioritization and criticality tools (Urgency & Priority).

**Responsibilities**

1. Analyze and plan testing:
**‚óè **Participate in requirements analysis and evaluation of tasks under test;
**‚óè **Developing testing strategies and plans, including defining approaches to Testing of new features and their improvement.

2. WEB application testing: 
**‚óè **Conducting manual and automated testing of WEB functionality;
**‚óè **Participating in the analysis of requirements and evaluation of tested tasks;
**‚óè **Developing testing strategies and plans, including defining approaches to testing new features and improving them applications;
**‚óè **Creation, execution and support of test artifacts (test cases, test plans);
**‚óè **Functional, regression, integration, load and smoke testing smoke-testing.

3. Work with microservice architecture:
**‚óè **Testing of microservices and interaction between them;
**‚óè **Develop and execute tests for APIs and integration tests between microservices.

4. Integration testing with external services:
**‚óè **Testing of integration with external services, including payment systems, AML systems and other services;
**‚óè **Verification of correctness of interaction and data processing from third-party services.

5. Work with admin panels and BO (Back Office) systems:
**‚óè **Testing of main interfaces and functionalities of admin panels.

6. Test automation:
**‚óè **Development and support of auto-tests;
**‚óè **Creation and support of automation scripts for separate parts of WEB-application (Unit tests);
**‚óè **Support and improvement of CI/CD processes to ensure stable and fast release cycle.

7. Analyzing and reporting:
**‚óè **Analyzing test results and reporting on test passes (TestRail);
**‚óè **Maintaining bug reports and tracking statuses in the bug tracking system (Jira);
**‚óè **Maintaining and keeping test data up to date (Confluence).

8. Interaction with the development team:
**‚óè **Collaborate with developers, business analysts, designers, and other team members to understand requirements and their solutions;
**‚óè **Participate in meetings, discussions, planning, and process improvements in development and testing (SCRUM artifacts).

9. Interaction with the Helpdesk team

